<paragraph id="8BEF36930372EF6C1CE97B59FC976905" blockId="13.[372,1215,993,1092]" box="[733,854,1066,1092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">
<figureCitation id="136B2A160372EF6C1CE97B59FC976905" box="[733,854,1066,1092]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1387,808,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-165@14.[189,1398,800,1854]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 8. A–F. Drassodes persianus sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MHNG). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Chelicera, prolateral view. C, E. Epigyne, ventral view.D, F. Epigyne, dorsal view. – G–H. D. longispinus Marusik &amp; Logunov, 1995, ♀ (PSU-8263). G. Epigyne, ventral view. H. Epigyne, dorsal view. Abbreviation: Lm = lateral margin. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; C = 0.2 mm; E–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4906029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4906029/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Fig. 8A–F</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A65180372EF6C1E897B1FFE676809" pageId="13" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEF36930372EF6C1E897B1FFEF769C7" blockId="13.[189,310,1132,1158]" box="[189,310,1132,1158]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">
<heading id="D0A781FF0372EF6C1E897B1FFEF769C7" bold="true" box="[189,310,1132,1158]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="81" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B924EA810372EF6C1E897B1FFEF769C7" bold="true" box="[189,310,1132,1158]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36930372EF6C1E897BEFFE676809" blockId="13.[187,1407,1180,1352]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">
The epigyne of the new species is most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100372EF6C1D487BEEFABE69F6" authority="Marusik &amp; Logunov, 1995" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Logunov" authorityYear="1995" box="[892,1407,1180,1207]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinus">
<emphasis id="B924EA810372EF6C1D487BEEFBED69F7" box="[892,1068,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">D. longispinus</emphasis>
Marusik &amp; Logunov, 1995
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="136B2A160372EF6C1EF27BB3FE84699B" box="[198,325,1216,1242]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[189,1387,808,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-165@14.[189,1398,800,1854]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 8. A–F. Drassodes persianus sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MHNG). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Chelicera, prolateral view. C, E. Epigyne, ventral view.D, F. Epigyne, dorsal view. – G–H. D. longispinus Marusik &amp; Logunov, 1995, ♀ (PSU-8263). G. Epigyne, ventral view. H. Epigyne, dorsal view. Abbreviation: Lm = lateral margin. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; C = 0.2 mm; E–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4906029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4906029/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Fig. 8G–H</figureCitation>
) but can be distinguished by the rounded posterior margin of the median plate being slightly extended beyond the epigastric furrow (vs straight, not extended), the relatively long atrium (width/length ratio as shown by broken lines ca 1.4 vs 2) and the lateral margins (
<emphasis id="B924EA810372EF6C1D8F7A7AFC216863" box="[955,992,1289,1314]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Lm</emphasis>
) S-shaped with lateral indentations (vs almost parallel).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A65180372EF6C1E897A1CFD87689F" pageId="13" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEF36930372EF6C1E897A1CFE8568C8" blockId="13.[189,324,1391,1417]" box="[189,324,1391,1417]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">
<heading id="D0A781FF0372EF6C1E897A1CFE8568C8" bold="true" box="[189,324,1391,1417]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="81" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B924EA810372EF6C1E897A1CFE8568C8" bold="true" box="[189,324,1391,1417]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36930372EF6C1E897AECFD87689F" blockId="13.[189,1398,1439,1502]" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">
The specific epithet is an adjective and refers to the historical region of the Middle East, located in eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F34776030372EF6C1E897AB0FEA1689C" box="[189,352,1475,1501]" name="Iraq" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Mesopotamia</collectingCountry>
, which is now 
<collectingCountry id="F34776030372EF6C1C3B7AB7FD83689F" box="[527,578,1476,1502]" name="Iran" pageId="13" pageNumber="81">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
